Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (HII) Analysts See $2.62 EPS


					

						July 28, 2017 - By Peter Erickson


Investors sentiment decreased to 0.91 in 2016 Q4. Its down 0.30, from 1.21 in 2016Q3. It fall, as 48 investors sold Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc shares while 139 reduced holdings. 70 funds opened positions while 101 raised stakes. 39.80 million shares or 1.66% less from 40.48 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported.
 Twin Tree Mngmt L P owns 0% invested in Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII) for 2,521 shares. Provise Management Ltd Liability Corp holds 2,687 shares. Herndon Ltd Co invested 0.01% in Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII). 2,268 were reported by Wexford L P. Airain invested in 0.02% or 1,564 shares. Apriem accumulated 0% or 50 shares. Asset Mgmt One Limited stated it has 0.04% of its portfolio in Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII). Moreover, Northcoast Asset Mngmt Lc has 0.05% invested in Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII). Credit Suisse Ag accumulated 50,288 shares. Renaissance Technology Ltd Co stated it has 433,200 shares. Montag A And Associates holds 0.1% or 4,430 shares in its portfolio. 2,573 were accumulated by Pitcairn Co. 3,446 are held by Charter Co. Axa holds 0.11% of its portfolio in Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII) for 124,500 shares. Goldman Sachs Grp reported 0.05% stake.

Since March 3, 2017, it had 1 buying transaction, and 6 selling transactions for $3.87 million activity. Shares for $2.40 million were sold by Kastner Christopher D on Thursday, May 4. Cuccias Brian J. had sold 4,137 shares worth $858,386 on Friday, March 24. The insider Smith Michael Stephen sold $28,400. Wyatt D R sold 850 shares worth $167,960. The insider ERMATINGER WILLIAM R sold $1.09 million.






Analysts await Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII) to report earnings on August, 3 before the open. They expect $2.62 EPS, up 12.93 % or $0.30 from last year’s $2.32 per share. HII’s profit will be $120.51 million for 19.35 P/E if the $2.62 EPS becomes a reality. After $1.87 actual EPS reported by Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts 40.11 % EPS growth. The stock decreased 0.32% or $0.65 during the last trading session, reaching $202.84. About shares traded. Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII) has risen 26.91% since July 28, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 10.21% the S&P500.
Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII) Ratings Coverage
Among 9 analysts covering Huntington Ingalls Industries (NYSE:HII), 4 have Buy rating, 1 Sell and 4 Hold. Therefore 44% are positive. Huntington Ingalls Industries had 23 analyst reports since August 7, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The company was maintained on Friday, November 6 by Deutsche Bank. The company was maintained on Friday, May 5 by Cowen & Co. The firm earned “Buy” rating on Wednesday, September 7 by Citigroup. Stifel Nicolaus downgraded the stock to “Sell” rating in Tuesday, May 24 report. Citigroup downgraded Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII) on Wednesday, March 1 to “Neutral” rating. The firm earned “Buy” rating on Thursday, January 12 by Bank of America. The stock of Huntington Ingalls Industries Inc (NYSE:HII) has “Buy” rating given on Monday, July 11 by Deutsche Bank. Credit Suisse upgraded the stock to “Neutral” rating in Monday, January 18 report. As per Monday, July 17, the company rating was maintained by Cowen & Co. As per Friday, June 16, the company rating was maintained by Cowen & Co.
Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. is a military shipbuilding firm and a well-known provider of professional services to partners in government and industry. The company has market cap of $9.33 billion. The Company’s business consists of the design, construction, repair and maintenance of nuclear-powered ships and non-nuclear ships for the United States Navy and coastal defense surface ships for the United States Coast Guard, as well as the refueling and overhaul and inactivation of nuclear-powered ships for the United States Navy. It has a 17.1 P/E ratio. It operates through three divisions: Ingalls Shipbuilding , Newport News Shipbuilding (Newport News) and Technical Solutions.
