In Volatile Markets Do Analysts Think You Should Buy Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. (NYSE:HII)?


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Sunday, 23 Jul 2017 07:08 AM  / 0 Comments




Following U.S. election volatility some analysts have updated their recommended target prices on shares of Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. (NYSE:HII).  	 According to the most recently released broker notes, 3 analysts have a rating of “strong buy” on the stock, 1 analysts “buy”, 6 analysts “neutral”, 1 analysts “sell” and 1 analysts “strong sell”. 	  



Latest Recommended Buy/Sell Side Ratings:
05/05/2017 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Credit Suisse.  They now have a USD 206 price target on the stock.
03/01/2017 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Citigroup.  They now have a USD 220 price target on the stock.
02/17/2017 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Stifel Nicolaus.  They now have a USD 150 price target on the stock.
01/12/2017 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Bank of America Merrill Lynch.
09/20/2016 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Cowen.  They now have a USD 165 price target on the stock.
08/05/2016 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Wells Fargo. 
06/17/2016 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at UBS.  They now have a USD 180 price target on the stock.
05/09/2016 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Barclays.  They now have a USD 135 price target on the stock.
04/12/2016 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Goldman Sachs.  They now have a USD 148 price target on the stock.
01/20/2016 – Guggenheim began new coverage on Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 145 price target on the stock.
11/06/2015 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Deutsche Bank.  They now have a USD 157 price target on the stock.
05/11/2015 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Sanford C. Bernstein.  They now have a USD 142 price target on the stock.
05/09/2014 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at JP Morgan.  They now have a USD 113 price target on the stock.
05/06/2014 – Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Zacks.  They now have a USD 109.3 price target on the stock.
03/05/2014 – Morgan Stanley began new coverage on Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 110 price target on the stock.
The share price of Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. (NYSE:HII) was up +1.08% during the last trading session, with a day high of 202.14. 235031 shares were traded on Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc.’s last session. 
The stock’s 50 day moving average is 192.12 and its 200 day moving average is 199.05. The stock’s market capitalization is 9.27B. Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. has a 52-week low of 146.52 and a 52-week high of 220.68.



Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc. is a military shipbuilding company and a provider of professional services to partners in government and industry. The Company’s business consists of the design, construction, repair and maintenance of nuclear-powered ships and non-nuclear ships for the United States Navy and coastal defense surface ships for the United States Coast Guard, as well as the refueling and overhaul and inactivation of nuclear-powered ships for the United States Navy. It operates through three segments: Ingalls Shipbuilding (Ingalls), Newport News Shipbuilding (Newport News) and Technical Solutions. Its Ingalls segment includes its non-nuclear ship design, construction, repair and maintenance businesses. Its Newport News includes all of its nuclear ship design, construction, overhaul, refueling, and repair and maintenance businesses. Its Technical Solutions segment provides a range of professional services to the governmental, energy, and oil and gas markets.


